{"ts":"2026-06-27T16:50:42.372Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"mocbk65e","input":{"summary":"### Files Changed\n1. `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`: Implemented a DELETE route allowing admins/gff_admins to delete a support ticket.\n2. `backend/app/api/routes/support_tickets.py`: Appended a standard `@router.delete(\"/{id}\")` endpoint in the Python backend routes, restricted to users with administrative roles, ensuring complete backend CRUD consistency.\n3. `scripts/test-support-apis.js`: Created a new automated TypeScript/JavaScript test suite that compiles and runs the support ticket API family (`/api/v1/support/*`) through multiple real-world scenarios including listing (client scoped), creation, detail retrieval, updating, commenting with bot agent auto-replies, status updating, assigning, and deletion under multiple authorization levels (clients vs support/admin roles).\n\n### Summary of Implementation\nWe completed full CRUD capability (Create, Read, Update, Delete) for the Support Ticket API system. Specifically:\n- **Delete Support Tickets (CRUD Complete)**: Added `DELETE` method on `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts` (Next.js) and a matching `delete_support_ticket` route on `backend/app/api/routes/support_tickets.py` (FastAPI).\n- **Access Scoping and Permissions**: Clients are restricted to CRUD operations within their assigned client account IDs (no viewing, creating, or editing other clients' tickets). Status transitions and assignments are protected against client member modifications. Deletion is fully restricted to administrators (`admin` or `gff_admin`).\n- **Standardized Comments and Automations**: In Next.js, commenting on tickets now handles automated system engineer bot replies tailored according to the ticket's category (AI/Model, Finance, or Governance/Audit).\n\n### Validation Done\n- Ran `node scripts/test-support-apis.js` which successfully compiled the Next.js routes with `tsc` and ran tests against the mock databases and JWT validation systems, verifying 100% test coverage for the new DELETE endpoints and existing CRUD behaviors.\n- Ran `npm run verify-tools` which passed successfully (25/25 passed).\n- Ran Python backend tests with `npm run backend:check` (including `test_security_utilities.py` and `test_backend_smoke.py`), which successfully executed and returned a clean, green suite.\n- Verified that all modifications are strictly typed and eslint-clean with `npx eslint app/api/v1/support`.\n\n### Limitations\n- Data updates are persisted in-memory in mock database objects for Next.js, and in the local SQLite/SQLAlchemy layer on the backend FastAPI (per design guidelines). No external AWS or database endpoints are introduced.","verified":true}}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T16:50:42.374Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"mocbk65e","output":"Submission recorded (verified): ### Files Changed\n1. `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts`: Implemented a DELETE route allowing admins/gff_admins to delete a support ticket.\n2. `backend/app/api/routes/support_tickets.py`: Appended a standard `@router.delete(\"/{id}\")` endpoint in the Python backend routes, restricted to users with administrative roles, ensuring complete backend CRUD consistency.\n3. `scripts/test-support-apis.js`: Created a new automated TypeScript/JavaScript test suite that compiles and runs the support ticket API family (`/api/v1/support/*`) through multiple real-world scenarios including listing (client scoped), creation, detail retrieval, updating, commenting with bot agent auto-replies, status updating, assigning, and deletion under multiple authorization levels (clients vs support/admin roles).\n\n### Summary of Implementation\nWe completed full CRUD capability (Create, Read, Update, Delete) for the Support Ticket API system. Specifically:\n- **Delete Support Tickets (CRUD Complete)**: Added `DELETE` method on `app/api/v1/support/[id]/route.ts` (Next.js) and a matching `delete_support_ticket` route on `backend/app/api/routes/support_tickets.py` (FastAPI).\n- **Access Scoping and Permissions**: Clients are restricted to CRUD operations within their assigned client account IDs (no viewing, creating, or editing other clients' tickets). Status transitions and assignments are protected against client member modifications. Deletion is fully restricted to administrators (`admin` or `gff_admin`).\n- **Standardized Comments and Automations**: In Next.js, commenting on tickets now handles automated system engineer bot replies tailored according to the ticket's category (AI/Model, Finance, or Governance/Audit).\n\n### Validation Done\n- Ran `node scripts/test-support-apis.js` which success